”vLf<?php exit; ?>a:1:{s:7:"content";a:137:{s:10:"_edit_last";a:1:{i:0;s:2:"12";}s:10:"_edit_lock";a:1:{i:0;s:13:"1636490339:12";}s:17:"_wp_page_template";a:1:{i:0;s:7:"default";}s:16:"alternate_header";a:1:{i:0;s:38:"Donor Sites for Custom Engraved Bricks";}s:17:"_alternate_header";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a3f8241d5db";}s:10:"subheading";a:1:{i:0;s:26:"Frequently Asked Questions";}s:11:"_subheading";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a3f82e1d5dc";}s:18:"use_featured_image";a:1:{i:0;s:1:"0";}s:19:"_use_featured_image";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a3de3f4bd26";}s:14:"call_to_action";a:1:{i:0;s:1:"0";}s:15:"_call_to_action";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55b61e91d31a1";}s:13:"dsq_thread_id";a:1:{i:0;s:0:"";}s:3:"faq";a:1:{i:0;s:1:"1";}s:4:"_faq";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a808f5b35cd";}s:18:"faq_0_faq_category";a:1:{i:0;s:0:"";}s:19:"_faq_0_faq_category";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80902b35ce";}s:27:"faq_0_faq_fields_0_question";a:1:{i:0;s:32:"How do we set up our Donor Site?";}s:28:"_faq_0_faq_fields_0_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:25:"faq_0_faq_fields_0_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:539:"First, you will need to <a href="/requestpassword/" target="_blank"> register</a> to use our Online Ordering System.&nbsp;Once you have registered and logged into your account, click "Donor Site Request" from one of the menu items listed.&nbsp;If you need assistance with registering, either go to <a href="//www.bricksrus.com/help" target="_blank">our help section</a> or ask one of our representatives to send you an email on the information our system is looking for.&nbsp; We also have a Webinar service to walk you through the system.";}s:26:"_faq_0_faq_fields_0_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:27:"faq_0_faq_fields_1_question";a:1:{i:0;s:48:"Do we need to complete all of the questions now?";}s:28:"_faq_0_faq_fields_1_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:25:"faq_0_faq_fields_1_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:290:"No; if you do not have all of the information, you can return later to complete the form.&nbsp;Click on ‚ÄúSave My Information: I'll Come Back Later" to return to your form at a later time.&nbsp;When you log back into the Online Ordering System, your page will look the same as you left it.";}s:26:"_faq_0_faq_fields_1_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:27:"faq_0_faq_fields_2_question";a:1:{i:0;s:47:"What will be the URL address of our Donor Site?";}s:28:"_faq_0_faq_fields_2_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:25:"faq_0_faq_fields_2_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:724:"All of our donor sites start with www.bricksrus.com/donorsite/; from there, you can decide what 
to name your site.&nbsp;If your organization‚Äôs name is "Save The Whales," you can have your donor 
site URL as "www.bricksrus.com/donorsite/whales".&nbsp;We recommend keeping the URL as 
short as possible.&nbsp;You can confirm the name isn't already taken by viewing our Donor Site 
Donate page <a href="/fundraising/donate">here</a>.&nbsp;If you plan on advertising before we complete 
the site and wish to reserve the name, contact a Bricks R Us representative and he or she will 
have our Web Team reserve it.&nbsp;If a Donor Site's URL is not reserved, the name will not be 
guaranteed until the site is completed.";}s:26:"_faq_0_faq_fields_2_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:27:"faq_0_faq_fields_3_question";a:1:{i:0;s:73:"Does Bricks R Us provide the URL address of the Donor Site to our Donors?";}s:28:"_faq_0_faq_fields_3_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:25:"faq_0_faq_fields_3_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:402:"It's up to you.&nbsp;You have two choices: You can provide the URL to your donors or you can have your donors go to your main website and then provide a link that goes to the site we create (recommended).&nbsp;When our Web Team completes the site, they will attach two pictures that you can use on your Donor Site.&nbsp;The pictures will be of a brick with the writing "Click Here To Purchase A Brick."";}s:26:"_faq_0_faq_fields_3_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:27:"faq_0_faq_fields_4_question";a:1:{i:0;s:84:"Is it possible to not have our Donors go to your site and create a page on our site?";}s:28:"_faq_0_faq_fields_4_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:25:"faq_0_faq_fields_4_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:306:"Yes.&nbsp;We will still complete the Donor Site as we always do but we can provide a single line of code for your webmaster to add to a page on your server and it will work just as though they were on our site.&nbsp;You can request this code once the site is completed.&nbsp; This is called an iframe code.";}s:26:"_faq_0_faq_fields_4_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:27:"faq_0_faq_fields_5_question";a:1:{i:0;s:47:"How long does it take to create the Donor Site?";}s:28:"_faq_0_faq_fields_5_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:25:"faq_0_faq_fields_5_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:250:"One week!&nbsp; We used to have a two week turnaround and charge a $50 fee for a 48 hour turnaround but since our Donor Sites are so popular and are a big asset to our customers, we have pushed this time up so you can start selling that much quicker.";}s:26:"_faq_0_faq_fields_5_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:27:"faq_0_faq_fields_6_question";a:1:{i:0;s:29:"How do we pay for a web rush?";}s:28:"_faq_0_faq_fields_6_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:25:"faq_0_faq_fields_6_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:244:"Nothing!&nbsp; We have removed this fee and now turn all Donor Sites around within a week but if that isn't quick enough due to a function that you will need the Donor Site for, let us know and we will do everything possible to accommodate you.";}s:26:"_faq_0_faq_fields_6_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:27:"faq_0_faq_fields_7_question";a:1:{i:0;s:48:"How do we know when the Donor Site is completed?";}s:28:"_faq_0_faq_fields_7_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:25:"faq_0_faq_fields_7_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:190:"In approximately one week from submittal, our Web Team will send you an email advising the site has been completed.&nbsp;In that email, they will provide instructions on how to use the site.";}s:26:"_faq_0_faq_fields_7_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:27:"faq_0_faq_fields_8_question";a:1:{i:0;s:51:"Does Bricks R Us receive the money from our Donors?";}s:28:"_faq_0_faq_fields_8_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:25:"faq_0_faq_fields_8_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:228:"No.&nbsp;We do not receive any money until you submit the orders to us.&nbsp;After you submit the orders, we do not require payment until the bricks are going to be shipped.&nbsp;All money paid goes directly to the organization.";}s:26:"_faq_0_faq_fields_8_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:27:"faq_0_faq_fields_9_question";a:1:{i:0;s:35:"Can you accept credit cards for us?";}s:28:"_faq_0_faq_fields_9_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:25:"faq_0_faq_fields_9_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:390:"Yes, Bricks R Us Merchant Services acts just like PayPal with the exception the Donor is kept on the site to complete the payment.&nbsp; We will accept credit card payments for a particular month all monies collected will be paid by the 10th of the following month (minus transaction fees).&nbsp; Bricks R Us Merchant Services' fees are comparable to PayPal at 3.5% and .30 per transaction.";}s:26:"_faq_0_faq_fields_9_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:28:"faq_0_faq_fields_10_question";a:1:{i:0;s:83:"If we use Bricks R Us Merchant Services, how does that work in regards to payments.";}s:29:"_faq_0_faq_fields_10_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:26:"faq_0_faq_fields_10_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:344:"We will collect Donor Site monies for the current month and will transfer those funds (minus transaction fees) by the 10th of the following month.&nbsp; We will automatically place your funds in the account you specify.&nbsp; Bricks R Us does not hold any of your money and only receives payment for your order(s) before the bricks are shipped.";}s:27:"_faq_0_faq_fields_10_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:28:"faq_0_faq_fields_11_question";a:1:{i:0;s:77:"If we use Bricks R Us Merchant Services, how do we get Donor Payment reports?";}s:29:"_faq_0_faq_fields_11_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:26:"faq_0_faq_fields_11_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:204:"Our customers can log into their account within the Online Ordering System and create their own reports for any time-period.&nbsp; Report are live so you are able to retrieve up to the minute information.";}s:27:"_faq_0_faq_fields_11_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:28:"faq_0_faq_fields_12_question";a:1:{i:0;s:38:"How do our Donors pay for their brick?";}s:29:"_faq_0_faq_fields_12_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:26:"faq_0_faq_fields_12_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:378:"Donors are able to process their payments with a check or credit card.&nbsp;If paying with a check, they will input their check number in the system and receive an address to which they may mail their payment (your address).&nbsp; If paying with a credit card, they can pay through PayPal, or you can process the credit card payments if you have your own merchant account.&nbsp;";}s:27:"_faq_0_faq_fields_12_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:28:"faq_0_faq_fields_13_question";a:1:{i:0;s:21:"How does PayPal work?";}s:29:"_faq_0_faq_fields_13_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:26:"faq_0_faq_fields_13_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:590:"You create a PayPal account at <a href="http://www.paypal.com" target="_blank">Paypal</a>.&nbsp;PayPal (and all credit card merchants) charges a percentage of the transaction (usually 3%) plus a transaction fee (usually .30).&nbsp;PayPal allows you to accept all types of credit cards, and the money is deposited in your PayPal account.&nbsp;To receive the money, request it from PayPal.&nbsp;When filling out the Donor Site Request form, there is a field that asks for your login email with PayPal.&nbsp;Please do not provide your password.&nbsp;Bricks R Us has no affiliation with PayPal.";}s:27:"_faq_0_faq_fields_13_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:28:"faq_0_faq_fields_14_question";a:1:{i:0;s:68:"Do we need to change any settings with PayPal to use with your site?";}s:29:"_faq_0_faq_fields_14_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:26:"faq_0_faq_fields_14_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:153:"Yes.&nbsp;We have provided instructions <a href="http://www.bricksrus.com/help" target="_blank">here</a> under the Donor Site section (Accepting PayPal).";}s:27:"_faq_0_faq_fields_14_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:28:"faq_0_faq_fields_15_question";a:1:{i:0;s:86:"What if we already have a PayPal account?  Can we use that account with your site too?";}s:29:"_faq_0_faq_fields_15_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:26:"faq_0_faq_fields_15_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:98:"Yes.&nbsp;however, you would ignore Step 5 (in the help section above) and keep "Auto Return" off.";}s:27:"_faq_0_faq_fields_15_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:28:"faq_0_faq_fields_16_question";a:1:{i:0;s:42:"Will you answer questions from our Donors?";}s:29:"_faq_0_faq_fields_16_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:26:"faq_0_faq_fields_16_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:262:"Yes.&nbsp;We have a live chat button to assist your Donors.&nbsp;We will only provide any information that already exists on your Donor Site and/or how the process works.&nbsp;We do not provide dates of ordering or installation because that process is up to you.";}s:27:"_faq_0_faq_fields_16_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:28:"faq_0_faq_fields_17_question";a:1:{i:0;s:87:"What can I do if I don‚Äôt receive a PayPal confirmation of an order placed by a donor?";}s:29:"_faq_0_faq_fields_17_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:26:"faq_0_faq_fields_17_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:898:"<p>When we first created the Donor Sites, a record of an order would be generated after the order is paid with PayPal.&nbsp;This is the way most PayPal sites operate.&nbsp;However, there were concerns of donors paying for the order through PayPal, but not returning to the Donor Site to complete their brick order.&nbsp;Thus, organizations would receive a PayPal confirmation of purchase, but not an order confirmation.&nbsp;</p><p>Due to the above, we changed the recording to occur before the donor is sent to PayPal.&nbsp;You will be able to see a record of everyone who‚Äôs processed an order through the Donor Site.&nbsp;</p><p>Thanks to this process, if you receive an order confirmation from the Donor Site, but not a PayPal confirmation, you can return to the Donor Site to retrieve the donor‚Äôs contact information.&nbsp;You can then follow up with the donor regarding their purchase.</p>";}s:27:"_faq_0_faq_fields_17_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:28:"faq_0_faq_fields_18_question";a:1:{i:0;s:72:"If we process our own credit cards, how do we retrieve that information?";}s:29:"_faq_0_faq_fields_18_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:26:"faq_0_faq_fields_18_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:238:"All of the credit card information is captured from the Donor and can be retrieved by logging into our secure/encrypted Online Ordering System.&nbsp;Once you login, place your cursor over the "Reports" tab and click on "Donor Payments.‚Äù";}s:27:"_faq_0_faq_fields_18_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:28:"faq_0_faq_fields_19_question";a:1:{i:0;s:62:"Will we receive a confirmation when a Donor purchases a brick?";}s:29:"_faq_0_faq_fields_19_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:26:"faq_0_faq_fields_19_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:366:"Yes.&nbsp;Our system will automatically send an email notifying you that a donation was made.&nbsp;The email will have the donor's information, donation amount, type of payment, inscription and reference number (where it is located in your account within the Online Ordering System).&nbsp; You can also download the Bricks R Us app for notifications through the app.";}s:27:"_faq_0_faq_fields_19_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:16:"faq_0_faq_fields";a:1:{i:0;s:2:"26";}s:17:"_faq_0_faq_fields";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80911b35cf";}s:11:"outside_url";a:1:{i:0;s:1:"0";}s:12:"_outside_url";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55e46ef3140bd";}s:20:"_yoast_wpseo_focuskw";a:1:{i:0;s:22:"custom engraved bricks";}s:18:"_yoast_wpseo_title";a:1:{i:0;s:42:"Custom Engraved Bricks - FAQ | Bricks R Us";}s:21:"_yoast_wpseo_metadesc";a:1:{i:0;s:124:"Bricks R Us helps make your brick fundraiser a success with Donor Sites. Visit our frequently asked questions to learn more!";}s:20:"_yoast_wpseo_linkdex";a:1:{i:0;s:2:"35";}s:31:"_yoast_wpseo_focuskw_text_input";a:1:{i:0;s:22:"custom engraved bricks";}s:15:"full_size_image";a:1:{i:0;s:1:"0";}s:16:"_full_size_image";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_5643743c360d7";}s:18:"show_image_on_page";a:1:{i:0;s:1:"0";}s:19:"_show_image_on_page";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_564dead7501e4";}s:26:"_yoast_wpseo_content_score";a:1:{i:0;s:2:"60";}s:16:"_wpml_word_count";a:1:{i:0;s:39:"{"total":119,"to_translate":{"es":119}}";}s:21:"_wpml_media_duplicate";a:1:{i:0;s:1:"0";}s:20:"_wpml_media_featured";a:1:{i:0;s:1:"0";}s:28:"faq_0_faq_fields_20_question";a:1:{i:0;s:53:"Will you engrave the brick when the donation is made?";}s:29:"_faq_0_faq_fields_20_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:26:"faq_0_faq_fields_20_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:160:"No.&nbsp;The inscription and all of the Donor Information goes into your account within the Online Ordering System and stays there until you "submit" the order.";}s:27:"_faq_0_faq_fields_20_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:28:"faq_0_faq_fields_21_question";a:1:{i:0;s:28:"Are your Donor Sites secure?";}s:29:"_faq_0_faq_fields_21_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:26:"faq_0_faq_fields_21_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:180:"Yes.&nbsp;All Donor Sites are directed to a site beginning with https:// (this is what all secure sites start with).&nbsp; In fact, all Bricks R Us pages on our website are secure.";}s:27:"_faq_0_faq_fields_21_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:28:"faq_0_faq_fields_22_question";a:1:{i:0;s:91:"Is there another way to get notifications when a Donor purchases a brick on our Donor Site?";}s:29:"_faq_0_faq_fields_22_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:26:"faq_0_faq_fields_22_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:261:"Yes.&nbsp; We are the only engraving company that has an Apple and Android app.&nbsp; You can download the app by searching for "Bricks R Us".&nbsp; Our app mirrors the Online Ordering System and will also send you a notification when a purchase is made online.";}s:27:"_faq_0_faq_fields_22_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:28:"faq_0_faq_fields_23_question";a:1:{i:0;s:55:"What is a discount code in relation to the Donor Sites?";}s:29:"_faq_0_faq_fields_23_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:26:"faq_0_faq_fields_23_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:304:"Using the Online Ordering System, our customers can make active and program a discount code for their Donor Site.&nbsp; A discount code is given to their donors to receive a certain discount (percentage or dollars) for either a certain event or maybe they want to trace if a marketing program is working.";}s:27:"_faq_0_faq_fields_23_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:28:"faq_0_faq_fields_24_question";a:1:{i:0;s:110:"We want to provide an option for our Donors to purchase additional brick(s) for their home.  Is this possible?";}s:29:"_faq_0_faq_fields_24_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:26:"faq_0_faq_fields_24_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:250:"We provide Souvenir Bricks (small, size of your palm), Donor Bricks (regular size bricks) and Donor Certificates.&nbsp; These can either be sent directly to our customer or to each Donor.&nbsp; If to each Donor, an additional shipping fee is charged.";}s:27:"_faq_0_faq_fields_24_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}s:28:"faq_0_faq_fields_25_question";a:1:{i:0;s:61:"What if we have a problem with our Donor Site when it's live?";}s:29:"_faq_0_faq_fields_25_question";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a8091eb35d0";}s:26:"faq_0_faq_fields_25_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:258:"If you have an issue with your Donor Site and it's after hours, just give us a call and advise it's an emergency; we'll call you back as soon as possible.&nbsp; To date, our sites have never been off-line but if there's a problem, we are always here for you!";}s:27:"_faq_0_faq_fields_25_answer";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55a80923b35d1";}}}